Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 10/19/98
----------------------------------------

Finished writing the first version of the splicer code.  This version can
correctly merge two bitstreams together, re-generating the anchor frames and
B-frames if necessary.  The resulting bitstream can be decoded with mpeg2play
as well as our own decoder.

There are still quite some bugs to fix and items to add or improve, including:
  - temporal reference adjustment
  - bit rate conversion
  - better recode mode decision (currently we use intra MB whenever the
    original macroblock type cannot be reused.)
  - more efficient bit buffer handling
  - more efficient variable length decoding
  - overall re-structuring to handle generic splicing cases

